make output processable by less -r/-R

The 'less' command (with -r or -R option) behaves wrongly when color setting is applied to several subsequent lines (less -R colorizes only first line, while behavior of less -r is undefined).
Let's force cwdiff to output color-setting-control-characters for each line (not for set of subsequent lines) to make its output compatible with less -r/-R.
